-- Hydrogenics $92 Million Fuel-Cell Sale is Largest Order to Date
-- B y   E h r e n   G o o s s e n s
-- 2012-10-03T20:57:32Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-10-03/hydrogenics-92-million-fuel-cell-sale-is-largest-order-to-date.html
Hydrogenics Corp., a Canadian fuel-
cell maker, agreed to sell as much as $92 million of hydrogen
propulsion systems to an unidentified customer, its largest
contract to date.  The sale includes a $36 million design and manufacturing
contract and $13 million of equipment, Mississauga, Ontario-
based Hydrogenics said today in a statement. The customer may
also buy as much as $43 million of hardware and services over 10
years.  To contact the reporter on this story:
